ook at:\n\n1. The widgetbook registration\n2. The BDD test files\n3. The E2E sen
d_message flow\n4. Check if `ImBloc` is registered as factory vs singleton - the
spec says it should be singleton for socket lifecycle\n5. Check the design syste
m exports\n\nActually, looking at di.dart, `ImBloc` is registered as `registerFa
ctory`, but according to flutter.md:\n"涉及 Socket、WebSocket、长连接的 BLoC 必
须提升到 App 级别"\n\nAnd in app.dart it\'s created via `getIt<ImBloc>()`. With 
`registerFactory`, every `getIt<ImBloc>()` call creates a new instance. But in a
pp.dart it\'s only called once in the MultiBlocProvider. However, the issue is t
hat if anyone else calls `getIt<ImBloc>()`, they\'d get a different instance. Mo
re importantly, the spec examples use `registerLazySingleton` or `registerFactor
y` but the key point is that it should be a singleton.\n\nWait, looking more car
efully at app.dart line 34: `BlocProvider(create: (_) => getIt<ImBloc>())` - thi
s creates it once at app startup and it\'s maintained as a singleton by BlocProv
ider. Since it\'s registered as Factory, `getIt<ImBloc>()` will create a new ins
tance each time it\'s called. But within BlocProvider, it\'s called once during 
create. The risk is if any other code calls `getIt<ImBloc>()`.\n\nActually, look
ing at the flutter.md spec more carefully:\n```\n// ❌ 错误：ChatPage 每次进入都
创建新 Bloc，退出即断开 Socket\nBlocProvider(\n  create: (_) => getIt<ImBloc>(),
\n  child: const ChatPage(),\n)\n```\n\nIf ImBloc is registered as Factory, `get
It<ImBloc>()` creates a new instance every time. This is dangerous because if so
meone accidentally calls `getIt<ImBloc>()` in ChatPage (as shown in the anti-pat
tern), they\'d get a new instance. The safe approach is `registerLazySingleton<I
mBloc>`.\n\nBut wait - in the current app.dart, the BlocProvider is at the app l
evel, so it only creates once. But the registration as Factory means anyone call
ing `getIt<ImBloc>()` outside of that provider gets a different instance. This i
